questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a payment processing service intermittently fails to record audit logs and payment failure statuses in the database during downstream remote gateway timeouts.

Here is the core code snippet:

java
@Service
public class PaymentService {
    @Autowired
    private PaymentRepository paymentRepo;
    @Autowired
    private AuditLogger auditLogger;

    @Transactional
    public void processPayment(String paymentId) {
        try {
            paymentRepo.updateStatus(paymentId, "PROCESSING");
            callDownstreamGateway(paymentId);
        } catch (RemoteTimeoutException e) {
            handleFailure(paymentId, e);
        }
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void handleFailure(String paymentId, Exception e) {
        paymentRepo.updateStatus(paymentId, "FAILED");
        auditLogger.logFailure(paymentId, e.getMessage());
        throw new PaymentProcessingException("Gateway failed", e);
    }
}
